BFN 

  [Text] Narita, Chiba Pref., June 18 KYODO -- Former 
defense chief Taku Yamasaki returned home Saturday [18 June)( 
night via Beijing from a visit to North Korea. 
  Yamasaki, a Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) member of the 
House of Representatives and former director general of the 
Defense Agency, had met senior officials of the (North) Korean 
Workers' Party to press for a diplomatic solution to the dispute 
over North Korea's suspected nuclear arms program. 
  Also returning home was Yoichi Tani, another LDP lawmaker 
who 
accompanied Yamasaki on the visit to Pyongyang. 

